         <div>
            <entry xml:id="L7df37f1314d84983873ea44ffd820ed1" n="408">
               <form>
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ለይ</foreign>
               </form>
               <sense xml:lang="la" source="#dillmann" xml:id="Dmain"> <gramGrp> <pos expand="Substantivum">subst.</pos> </gramGrp>, <gramGrp> <gen value="not found">m.</gen> </gramGrp>, cui fere ubique <foreign xml:lang="grc">κόκκινον</foreign>, <foreign xml:lang="grc">κόκκινα</foreign> respondet. [Notionem <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la">
                            <quote> rubri </quote>
                        </cit> vel <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la">
                            <quote> coccinei coloris </quote>
                        </cit> semiticis radicibus <foreign xml:lang="gez">ለወየ፡</foreign> et vicinis haud inhaerere, omnes norunt. Peregrinum autem esse nomen <foreign xml:lang="gez">ለይ፡</foreign> nondum probatum est; neque enim audiendi sunt S. Bochartus (in <bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:Bochart1796HierozIII"/>
                            <citedRange unit="page"> 529</citedRange>
                        </bibl>; <bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:Bochart1796HierozIII"/>
                            <citedRange unit="page"> 669</citedRange>
                        </bibl>) et Ludolfus (in <lbl expand="lexicon">lex.</lbl> <lbl expand="columna">col.</lbl> 25), qui <foreign xml:lang="gez">ለይ፡</foreign> e voce <foreign xml:lang="grc">καλ</foreign>-<foreign xml:lang="grc">λαια</foreign> mutilatione ortum esse censent. Etymon semiticum persequenti mihi persuadeo, nomen <foreign xml:lang="gez">ለይ፡</foreign> vel <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la">
                            <quote> flexuosi </quote>
                        </cit> aliquid sive <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la">
                            <quote> tortuosi </quote>
                        </cit> ut cochleam, conchylium, vel plantam ut <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la">
                            <quote> convolvulum </quote>
                        </cit> aliamve herbam et arbusculam significare posse, e cujus radicibus vel foliis vel baccis Aethiopes colorem tinctorium coccineum petere soliti fuerint. Sed cum conchylii usum Aethiopibus notum fuisse ab antiquis scriptoribus non tradatur, mihi in eo acquiescendum videtur, ut <foreign xml:lang="gez">ለይ፡</foreign> nomen plantae tinctoriae (qualis <lbl expand="exempli gratia">ex. gr.</lbl> arbutus uva ursi est) fuerit, unde coccina factitia vel vestes coccinis similes confecta sunt. Etenim etiam <lbl expand="Vocabularium Aethiopicum, -a -a">Voc. Ae.</lbl> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ለይ፡</foreign> inter nomina plantarum recensitum et <foreign xml:lang="gez">ለይ፡ ዘ፡ ቀይሕ፡</foreign> eplicatum exhibent] <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la">
                            <quote> coccum </quote>
                        </cit>, <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la">
                            <quote> coccinum </quote>
                        </cit>, <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la">
                            <quote> textile </quote>
                        </cit> vel <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la">
                            <quote> filum coccineum </quote>
                        </cit>: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ከመ፡ ለይ፡</foreign> <foreign xml:lang="grc">ὡς κόκκινον</foreign> <ref cRef="Jes." loc="1,18">Jes. 1,18</ref>; <foreign xml:lang="gez">እመሂ፡ ለበስኪ፡ ለየ፡</foreign> <ref cRef="Jer." loc="4,30">Jer. 4,30</ref>; <foreign xml:lang="gez">አሠረት፡ ለየ፡ ውስተ፡ እዴሁ፡</foreign> <ref cRef="Gen." loc="38,28">Gen. 38,28</ref>; <ref cRef="Gen." loc="38,30">Gen. 38,30</ref>; <foreign xml:lang="grc">κόκκινα</foreign> <ref cRef="2 Reg." loc="1,24">2 Reg. 1,24</ref>; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ፐፒራለይ፡</foreign> <foreign xml:lang="grc">ἐρίου κοκκίνου</foreign> <ref cRef="Hebr." loc="9,19">Hebr. 9,19</ref>; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ፈትሉ፡ ዘለይ፡</foreign> <ref cRef="Sir." loc="45,11">Sir. 45,11</ref>; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሕብረ፡ ለይ፡</foreign> <ref cRef="2 Par." loc="2,7">2 Par. 2,7</ref>; <ref cRef="2 Par. " loc="3,14">2 Par.  3,14</ref>; praeterea creberrime in Octateucho: <ref cRef="Ex." loc="35,6">Ex. 35,6</ref>; <ref cRef="Ex." loc="35,25">Ex. 35,25</ref>; <ref cRef="Ex." loc="35,35">Ex. 35,35</ref>; <ref cRef="Ex." loc="36,9">Ex. 36,9</ref>; <ref cRef="Ex. " loc="36,10">Ex.  36,10</ref>; <ref cRef="Ex." loc="36,12">Ex. 36,12</ref>; <ref cRef="Ex." loc="36,32">Ex. 36,32</ref>; <ref cRef="Ex." loc="36,37">Ex. 36,37</ref>; <ref cRef="Ex." loc="37,3">Ex. 37,3</ref>; <ref cRef="Ex." loc="37,5">Ex. 37,5</ref>; <ref cRef="Lev." loc="14,4">Lev. 14,4</ref>; <ref cRef="Lev." loc="14,7">Lev. 14,7</ref>; <ref cRef="Num. " loc="4,8">Num.  4,8</ref>; <ref cRef="Num." loc="19,6">Num. 19,6</ref>; <ref cRef="Jos." loc="2,18">Jos. 2,18</ref>; <ref cRef="Jos." loc="2,21">Jos. 2,21</ref>, et in <ref cRef="Apoc." loc="17,4">Apoc. 17,4</ref>; <ref cRef="Apoc." loc="18,12">Apoc. 18,12</ref>. In versione Exodi recentiori vocabulo <foreign xml:lang="gez">ነት፡</foreign> (<lbl expand="quod videas">q.v.</lbl>) <foreign xml:lang="gez">ለይ፡</foreign> vocabulum substitui, ad <ref cRef="Ex." loc="25,4">Ex. 25,4</ref> annotavi. </sense>
               
